@node "Exp." "Menu explanation"

@{fg shine}File operations:@{fg text}
 @{b}New@{ub}          - Opens a new, blank window.
 @{b}Open@{ub}         - Opens a new window and filerequester and loads the selected
                file in the new window.
 @{b}Load@{ub}         - Opens the filerequester and loads the selected file in the
                current window.
 @{b}Revert@{ub}       - Loads the last saved version of the current loaded file.
 @{b}Save@{ub}         - Saves the current edited text.
 @{b}Save as@{ub}      - Opens the filerequester to be able to save the current
                edited text under a different name.
 @{b}Print@{ub}        - Prints the current edited text.
 @{b}Clear@{ub}        - Clears the current window. You'll be warned first.
 @{b}Close@{ub}        - Closes the current window.
 @{b}Close all@{ub}    - Closes all opened windows.
 @{b}Hide@{ub}         - Hides the current window. Select 'Reveal' in the
                @{"window manager" LINK "WindowManager"} to show it again.
 @{b}Add to
 project@{ub}      - Adds the current file to an opened project.
 @{b}Project
 Manager@{ub}      - This opens the @{"project manager" LINK "ProjectManager"} in which you are able to
                manage the documents which belong together.
 @{b}About@{ub}        - Opens the about requester with AmisED information.
 @{b}Iconify@{ub}      - Hides the AmisED environment and puts the amis icon on the
                workbench. Double click to activate the environment again.
                When iconifying no data will be lost (read disclaimer).
 @{b}Quit@{ub}         - This is the way to exit the AmisED program. You will be
                warned when edited data wasn't saved.

@{fg shine}Editing:@{fg text}
@{b} Cut@{ub}          - Removes the selected piece of text and saves it on the
                clipboard.
@{b} Copy@{ub}         - Copies the selected piece of text to the clipboard.
@{b} Paste@{ub}        - Pastes the contents of the clipboard.
@{b} Save block@{ub}   - Saves the selected piece of text via a filerequester.
@{b} Erase@{ub}        - Removes the selected piece of text. This function does not
                copy the text to the clipboard.
@{b} Block layout@{ub} - Allows center,left or right alignment for the selected
                piece of text.
@{b} Select all@{ub}   - Selects all text.
@{b} Select from
 cursor@{ub}       - Selects all text from the current cursor position to the end
                of the document.
@{b} Undo@{ub}         - Undoes a keyboard action.
@{b} Undo list@{ub}    - Show a list of keyboard actions in the @{"undo buffer" LINK "Editor..."}.
@{b} Redo@{ub}         - 'Redoes' a keyboard action removed with the undo function.
@{b} Insert file@{ub}  - Opens a filerequester and inserts the selected file after
                the current cursor position.
@{b} Insert
 ASCII code@{ub}   - Opens a requester in which you are able to type an ASCII
                code. The corresponding character will be inserted after the
                current cursor position.
@{b} Show ASCII
 code@{ub}         - Displays the ASCII code corresponding to the character on
                the current cursor's position.
@{b} Information@{ub}  - Displays information about the current document. In here you
                are also able to change its tooltypes.

@{fg shine}Searching:@{fg text}
 @{b}Find@{ub}         - Opens the @{"find-requester" LINK "Find"} in which you are able to fill in
                the text you want to search or replace.
 @{b}Find next@{ub}    - Searches the next occurence (relative to the cursor
                position) of the text you want to find.
 @{b}Find prev@{ub}    - Searches for the previous occurence (relative to the cursor
                position) of the text you want to find.
 @{b}Replace &
 next@{ub}         - (See Find next) and replaces it with the text you entered
                in the @{"find-requester" LINK "Find"}.
 @{b}Replace &
 prev@{ub}         - (See Find prev) and replaces it with the text you entered in
                the @{"find-requester" LINK "Find"}.
 @{b}Go to line@{ub}   - Opens a requester in which you are able to fill in the
                line number you want to go to.
 @{b}Go to
 bookmark@{ub}     - Goes to the bookmark you've set with Set bookmark.
 @{b}Set bookmark@{ub} - Sets a bookmark at the beginning of the current line.  A
                bookmark is a kind of flag which represents the current line
                number.
 @{b}Find
 functions@{ub}    - Opens the @{"find functions" LINK "FindFunctions"} window.

@{fg shine}Window:@{fg text}
 @{b}Viewer@{ub}       - Here you will find all the viewers AmisED supports.
                Selecting one of them will switch to that viewer.
 @{b}Bars@{ub}         - Here you are able to turn the 4 different bars on or off.
 @{b}Next@{ub}         - This will activate and pop up the next window.
 @{b}Previous@{ub}     - This will activate and pop up the previous window.
 @{b}Arrange@{ub}      - Here you will find 5 different ways of arranging the opened
                windows for a better overview.
 @{b}Window@{ub}
 @{b}Manager@{ub}      - This will open the @{"Window Manager" LINK "WindowManager"}.

@{fg shine}Miscellaneous:@{fg text}
@{b} Internal
 command@{ub}      - Opens the @{"Internal Command" LINK "Internalcommand"} window.
 @{b}Shell@{ub}        - Opens a @{"shell window" LINK "COM_Shell"} on the AmisED public screen.
 @{b}Execute
 command@{ub}      - Opens a @{"window" LINK "Executecommand"} in which you are able to execute a normal
                DOS command.
 @{b}Help@{ub}         - Opens the AmisED.guide on the AmisED public screen.
 @{b}Hunt file@{ub}    - Used in the C-viewer. If you place the cursor on an include
                command and select this option, AmisED will 'hunt' and open
                the include file.
 @{b}Create Guide
 Index@{ub}        - Opens a new window and creates an AmigaGuide index.
 @{b}Expand Tabs@{ub}  - Replaces all tabs inside a document with normal spaces.
 @{b}Insert
 current date@{ub} - Inserts the current date.
 @{b}Insert
 current time@{ub} - Inserts the current time.
 @{b}Folding@{ub}      - Used in the AmigaGuide viewer. If you place the cursor
                inside a node and select this option, the node will be
                hidden with only the node-name and lines remaining.
                Selecting it again will reveal the text.

@{fg shine}Macro:@{fg text}
 @{b}Start
 recording@{ub}    - Puts AmisED in macro recording mode. Keyboard actions will be
                recorded.
 @{b}Stop
 recording@{ub}    - Stops recording keyboard actions.
 @{b}Play@{ub}         - Plays the current active macro. See macro window.
 @{b}Play many@{ub}    - Opens a window in which you are able to give how many times
                AmisED should replay the current active macro.
 @{b}Macro window@{ub} - Opens the @{"macro window" LINK "Macro"}.

@{fg shine}Programming:@{fg text}
 @{b}Run@{ub}          - Runs (if compiled) the program belonging to the current
                loaded document.
 @{b}Compile@{ub}      - Executes the @{"chosen" LINK "Programming..."} compiler to compile the current loaded
                document.
 @{b}Assemble@{ub}     - Executes the @{"chosen" LINK "Programming..."} assembler to assemble the current
                loaded document.
 @{b}Link@{ub}         - Executes the @{"chosen" LINK "Programming..."} linker to link the current loaded
                document.
 @{b}Debug@{ub}        - Executes the @{"chosen" LINK "Programming..."} debugger to debug the current loaded
                document.
 @{b}First error@{ub}  - Jumps to the first error encountered during compiling or
                assembling.
 @{b}Next error@{ub}   - Jumps to the next error encountered during compiling or
                assembling.
 @{b}Prev error@{ub}   - Jumps to the previous error encountered during compiling or
                assembling.

@{fg shine}Settings:@{fg text}
 @{b}Toolbar@{ub}      - Opens the @{"toolbar" LINK "Toolbar"} settings window.
 @{b}Editor@{ub}       - Opens the @{"editor" LINK "Editor..."} settings window.
 @{b}Smart indent@{ub} - Opens the @{"smart indent" LINK "SmartIndent"} settings window.
 @{b}Keyboard@{ub}     - Opens the @{"keyboard" LINK "Keyboard..."} settings window.
 @{b}Menu@{ub}         - Opens the @{"menu" LINK "Menu..."} settings window.
 @{b}Screen@{ub}       - Opens the @{"screen" LINK "Screen"} settings window.
 @{b}Palette@{ub}      - Opens the @{"palette" LINK "Palette..."} settings window.
 @{b}Default
 fonts@{ub}        - Opens the @{"default fonts" LINK "DefaultFonts"} settings window.
 @{b}Programming@{ub}  - Opens the @{"programming" LINK "Programming..."} settings window.
 @{b}Miscellaneous@{ub}- Opens the @{"miscellaneous" LINK "Miscellaneous..."} settings window.
 @{b}Current
 window@{ub}       - Opens the @{"current window" LINK "CurrentWindow"} settings window.
 @{b}Load
 settings@{ub}     - Opens filerequester and loads the selected settings file.
 @{b}Save
 settings@{ub}     - Saves the current settings.
 @{b}Save
 settings as@{ub}  - Opens filerequester and saves the current settings under the
                selected name.

@endnode
@node "Windows" "Windows"

@{fg shine}Editing:@{fg text}
    @{"Find...            " LINK "Find"}
    @{"Find functions...  " LINK FindFunctions}
    @{"Undo list...       " LINK UndoList}
    @{"Macro...           " LINK Macro}

@{fg shine}Information:@{fg text}
    @{"Information...     " LINK "Information"}
    @{"About              " LINK About}

@{fg shine}Managers:@{fg text}
    @{"Project Manager    " LINK ProjectManager}
    @{"Window Manager     " LINK WindowManager}

@{fg shine}Settings:@{fg text}
    @{"Toolbar...         " LINK Toolbar}
    @{"Editor...          " LINK Editor...}
    @{"Smart Indent...    " LINK SmartIndent}
    @{"Keyboard...        " LINK Keyboard...}
    @{"Menu...            " LINK Menu...}
    @{"Screen...          " LINK Screen}
    @{"Palette...         " LINK Palette...}
    @{"Default fonts...   " LINK DefaultFonts}
    @{"Programming...     " LINK Programming...}
    @{"Miscellaneous...   " LINK "Miscellaneous..."}
